      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Thou art my refuge and my portion — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Thou only art both my refuge to defend me from all evil, and my portion to supply me with all the good which I need and desire; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "in the land of the living — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Even in this life, wherein I doubt not to see thy goodness, and more especially in the life to come. There is enough in God to answer all the necessities of this present time; we live in a world of dangers and wants, but what danger need we fear, if God is our refuge; and what wants, if he be our portion? Heaven, which alone deserves to be called ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the land of the living, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "will be to all believers both a refuge and a portion.",
        "children": []
      },
